children.text: The floor screed in this wet area has been completed, however there is no evidence that the substrate underneath has been properly waterproofed in accordance with building codes and standards.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the NCC's Building Code of Australia (BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and comply with AS 3740’.
Table 3.8.1.1 in the NCC/BCA shows that these areas must be waterproofed.
The builder must install waterproofing to these area as required by the NCC’s Building Code of Australia and Australian Standard AS 3740.
